# Nestlink Project Conventions

## Monorepo Layout

- `apps/web` — React + Vite web app (admin + resident portal)
- `apps/mobile` — Expo React Native app (iOS + Android)
- `packages/core` — Shared Zod schemas, types, utils (import as `@nestlink/core`)
- `packages/supabase` — DB types (import as `@nestlink/supabase`)
- `supabase/migrations/` — SQL migrations (numbered: `001_`, `002_`)
- `supabase/functions/` — Deno Edge Functions

## Local Supabase

Always connect to local Supabase during development:
- URL: `http://127.0.0.1:54321`
- Anon key: from `supabase status`
- `.env.local` must use these local values

## Code Patterns

### Supabase Queries (web)
```typescript
// Always use the shared supabase client from @/lib/supabase
import { supabase } from "@/lib/supabase";

// Wrap in useQuery — never fetch in component body
const { data } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["key", dependency],
  queryFn: async () => {
    const { data, error } = await supabase.from("table").select("*");
    if (error) throw error;
    return data;
  },
});
```

### Mutations
```typescript
const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: async (payload) => { /* ... */ },
  onSuccess: () => {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["key"] });
    toast.success("Done");
  },
  onError: (e: Error) => toast.error(e.message),
});
```

### New Page (web)
- Add route in `apps/web/src/App.tsx`
- Add nav item in `apps/web/src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`
- Add to global search entries in `apps/web/src/components/shared/CommandPalette.tsx`

### New Screen (mobile)
- File goes in `apps/mobile/app/<role>/<screen>.tsx`
- Add to tab layout in `apps/mobile/app/<role>/_layout.tsx`

## Realtime Subscriptions
Use the shared `useRealtimeQuery` hook for tables that need live updates:
```typescript
import { useRealtimeQuery } from "@/hooks/useRealtimeQuery";
const { data } = useRealtimeQuery("complaints", { queryKey, queryFn, pollIntervalMs: 15_000 });
```

## After Starting the Dev Server

Always verify the app launched by checking for the title text:
```bash
curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<title>Nestlink</title>'
# Expected output: <title>Nestlink</title>
```
If the command returns nothing, the server hasn't started or crashed. Check `pnpm dev` output.

## Multi-Society
- Active society stored in `useSocietyStore` (Zustand, persisted)
- Use `useSocietyStore(s => s.activeSocietyId)` in page queries instead of `profile.society_id`
- Admin can create new societies at `/admin/societies/new`
- Switcher lives in the sidebar — `<SocietySwitcher />`
